    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Controlled vocabularies in the form of a thesaurus, that are limited in the range of topics covered, but fit within the domain of a larger, broader, or more generic controlled vocabulary. A microthesaurus typically contains highly specialized terms that map to the hierarchical structure of the broader vocabulary at a high level node.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
